_ There were feasts in my childhood; since then we've been making them...
_ desascaulebi axla em{s} bavvobaic ("bavvobasac"), me axlac vaeteb.
lamara oniani-liareliani (svanuri enis laxuri dialekis carmomadgeneli) axali celi.
Speaker: Lamara Oniani-Liparteliani (LS). New Year. Video 29; (00:48:48:640_00:54:58:440).
The way I celebrate New Year...
zomxa lad... cina lade uxams xqled lxar.
We, Lashkhs, call New Year's Eve "Shushkhvami".
axali clis cina des "uxvams" veaxit laxelebi.
inars u er iri, zomxay cina lade, mama i alyr, migi dede i alyr bpars laqreltysa gqlax:
On that day, in the morning, Mother and Father used to tell us, children in bed:
dilit rom gatendeba, axali clis cina des, mama da eseni, dedaemi ("emi deda") da eseni bavvebs sacolebi gveubnebodnen:
"xuy uxam lok ogxmena," _ nay laydi: "sgay lok xy uxmu examnax",
"Many happy return of Shushkhvami!" We answered: "The same to you too";
_ i ale las zomxay sgobne lade.
- and it was New Year's Eve...
_ da es iqo axali clis cina des.
eno, zomxa let, ser i ximrold, i... atxy eyi i xasqxi mi.
Then, in the evening, used to get prepared; even now I do it so.
mere, axali clis ames, uve gavemzadebodit ("vemzadebodit") xolme, axlac ise vaeteb me.
I would boil a pig's head and jaw.
ales, lobyanars, ka xnqe, xaaurals, namcxarals, bileuls i eno acqob lapeks.
I would bake bean-bread, khachapuri, cakes, sweets and then I set a container for flour;
amas, lobianebs, gamovacxob xolme, xaaurebs, namcxvrebs, bileuls da mere vacqob pkvilis urels ("sapkviles").
I would set a container for flour,
I would fill it up with wheat flour.
iknka ls ami ka xocnixi, eei u xadsxi tetna lgras, tetne bambas.
I would pat it on top with a palm and put a white egg and some white wadding on it.
zemodan ase xelisguls gadavusmev xolme, imaze davdeb xolme tetr vercxs, tetr bambas.
pusna lemezr dyars xanqxi ka, abll, eis xadsxi, santels, bileulobas atasnairi
We would bake sacrificial bread resembling board and put a candle and lots of sweets on it;
uplis esacir urs gamovacxob xolme, ablasavit, imas vdeb, santels, atasnair bileulobas
i uusgs xidxi, xoa tala usgs.
and I took an apple, a good apple,
da vals vieb, lamaz ("arg tvali{s}") vals.
ales xurda tetrs ser ami ka xacxe, xurda tetr ale usgs,
put some coins around it, coins around the apple;
amas xurda puls ("tetrs") molet ase emovavleb ("emovarqam"), xurda puls am vals ("xurda tetrit am vals),
i xurda tetr lbrmbas u xadsxi ei i u xadsxi
and I would put it and cover it with coins...
da xurda pulit ("tetrit") daxunluls davdeb xolme imaze da davdeb xolme
and I used to put coins onto it even before.
mi atxe migi bp, migi ziadi xy xansu maqa, dolars er madi,
Now, when my son - God, give a long life to my Zviad! - gives me some dollars,
me axla emi bii ("bavvi"), emi zviadi didxans mimqopos mertma ("xvav xansamc mqavs"), dolars rom malevs,
dolarsi i xads lapeki i ser elodebi inars dsgi gatenebas.
I put them on the container for flour waiting for an early morning.
dolars davdeb xolme sapkvileze da uve velodebi dilas adre gatenebas.
mxi dabarebul maqa, mara mxi liqdld kora mxi xaer... mde...
I call a New Year well-wisher, but before he comes, a family well-wisher...should...that...
mevle dabarebuli mqavs, magram mevlis mosvlamde oaxis mevle unda... isa...
kora mxi migi nibnol giorgi maqa, manan gezal, eeu pdyas, i ka ri ale.
I have my grandchild Giorgi, Manana's son, as a family well-wisher; he would go out near there...
oaxis mevle emi vilivili ("badii") giorgi mqavs, mananas vili, ik axloi, da gava xolme es.
ka rid i mi laydi lapeks ka xaesxi iarnun i kmenu xugmxi brini... mdas... tepisa
We would go out and I take the prepared container for flour to the gate and I put some rice on... that... on the plate,
gavalt xolme da mec gamzadebul sapkviles gavian xolme iartan da garet davdgam xolme brinis... imas... tepi
"rbet, sasi qer emcadd, rbet, xy zay maxe ossrul miga ziadis, mia col-ils, miga mananas,
"God, let Sasashi's power be of great help to us; many happy returns of New Year to my Zviad, to his wife and children, to my Manana,
"merto, sasais ala egvecios, merto, bevri axali celi eusrule ems zviadis, mis col-vils, ems mananas,
mia kmarils i miga bpilars", _ i ami lamzrlu sga qednxi i sga korte i sga qedni giorgi i meled.
to her husband and children and to my children," - and with these words of praying I come back home;
mis kmar-vils da ems bavvebs", _ da ase locvit emoval xolme saxli da emova giorgic mevled.
Then a well-wisher comes, a well-wisher.
es'gi, mxi qedni i mxis lapeks xoxienixi qrmq i ao: "sgay lexyaenxas atxe ales, lapeks."
So, a well-wisher comes and I already have a flour container at the door and I tell him: "Now open your hands to this container".
ese igi, mevle mova da mevles sapkviles vaxvedreb artan da aba: "xeli gaixseni-metki ("axla amas, sapkviles")".
inars od mxi liqdld i er xignlxi, mi lapeks, od amenen xard, lelxas,
When I get up in the morning, before a well-wisher comes, while being here, in Lentekhi, I prepare
dilas mevlis mosvlamde rom avdgebi, me sapkviles, sanam ak viqavi, lenexi,
i xasqis lapeks i ka ris qrka i xuali:
a flour container and I go out and shout to him:
gavamzadebdi ("gavaetebdi") xolme sapkviles da gavdivar ari da veaxi:
korxenisa mxa migi a, _ xanda a:
My husband replies from the house, smiling:
saxlidan masuxobda ("mibrunebda") emi kmari, _ ise ("ase") ecineboda:
ineld baby ami gaqla, exen mua nanr, baby ami lda:
In old times our grandfather used to tell us something like this, I have heard from him, my grandfather used to say something like this:
velad babuac ase gveubneboda, imisgan makvs mosmenili, babuac ase ambobda ("iaxda"):
mrem nadobi, lama uma goi, laxam xamar goi,
"Peace to men, be cattle-shed full of cattle, pigsty full of pigs,
adamianis ("acis") mvidoba, boseli ("saumae") sakonlit ("umait") savse, saore orebit savse,
laktalir katlar goi, qr mar, bednyr!
hen-house full of chickens; open the door, you, lucky-man!"
sakatme katmebit savse, ari gamie, bedniero!
And we used to reply again, to reply:
"Peace for men, open the door, lucky-man!"
Having heard for the third time _
i emoaebda, sga qednl babua i ales xasqi miy ee i ami xasqi eleburad ales s
my grandfather would open the door and come in... and I do the same here, and I do all this as of old
da emoaebda, emovidoda babua da amas vaeteb mec ik da ase vaeteb veleburad amas qvelapers ("qvelas")
i lapeks ka xamne laqrlmq i sga xayixi, ka xabe.
And I would carry a flour container round the beds and I open my hand and offer it to everyone...
da sapkviles emovaareb xolme ("gavusvam") sacolebtan da imit xels vuxsni qvelas, mivacodeb xolme.
ami xasqi ales s i tetrl i xadsne os, bileul,
I do everything this way and I put their hands on sweets,
ase vaeteb amas qvelapers ("qvelas") da xurdebze ("tetrebze") davadebineb xolme xels ("os"), bileulze,
ere bil er maxe zay ere exdes miga oaxs.
so that my family might have sweet New Year.
rom bili axali celi moescros ems oaxs.
You should sit together with the well-wisher and say a toast.
mevlestan ertad unda dade, sadegrelo tkva.
The well-wisher would go around the rooms praying.
si laydi esgurixi, bils miacodeb i i xidxi ineli iks,
You, too, would sit, pass him sweets and I would take a glass of wine ,
enc dadebi, bils miacodeb da avieb xolme vinis ikas,
i xadsxui eenen, mzumi eni, xutlaryan, manetsi xaydin xadsd, atisi, iki.
and put as much money as we have - one, five, or ten lari note on the glass.
davdeb xolme imaze, ramdenic gekneba, xutlariani, manetsac bevrer vdebt, atsac, ikaze.
enonen eenen ampes xadsxi i iks ka xabe:
Then I put a candy on it and offer a glass:
mere imaze ampes vdeb xolme da ikas mivacodeb xolme:
"goi zaysu laxgnenaxi, kemiryand, cxemiryand, anmrteld, anmrteld, soyand,
"Have a full year, let it bring you increase in number, growth, health, physical fitness, luck,
"savse cels miadeki ("savse celsamc midgomixar"), momaebit, zrdit, anmrtelad, anmrtelad, svianad,
atasu zaysu ayna ladei lade", _ i ka xabxi, eis u xayi.
thousand returns of the day"' - and I would offer, I would open my hand.
atas cels ("atasimca celsamc") mogescros devandeli de", _ da mivacodeb xolme, imas xels gavuxsni xolme.
ei 'imzrli, eno lizld u xaer otsakara, yed saroas xahdxi, may meni,
He would say a toast, then I give him a present before he goes, I give him a shirt or whatever I have...
is sadegrelos iqvis xolme, mere casvlamde unda davasaukro, an erangs valev, rac mekneba,
lmre mua cinascar, euxe eis i tetrsi ka xasakari i maqopils pudxi meles.
I have prepared it beforehand, I would wrap it and present him some money too and then I let him go... he is pleased...
gamzadebuli makvs cinascar, evuxvev imas da pulsac ("tetrsac") vukni xolme da maqopils vuveb mevles.
This is how we celebrate New Year...
They had my children as well-wishers.
migi mezobel pepio li amenen, xoa mezobel maqa pepio, ea mxi manana las.
My neighbor Pepiko is here; I have a good neighbor Pepiko; Manana was her well-wisher.
emi mezobeli pepio aris ak, argi mezobeli mqavs pepio, imisi mevle manana iqo.
Zviad was a well-wisher to my another neighbour.
madonl meqda i ee ei aa mele las
I had Madona (a name) here and she, too, was a well-wisher.
madona mqavda da ik isic ("idev") mevle iqo
i inars mis i xamres ami... mdysa..., ampears, bileuls, s,
And in the morning I would prepare candies, sweets and all these things for all of them.
da dilas qvelas gavumzadebdi xolme ase... imai..., ampeebs, bileuls, qvelapers,
bpars ka xaqanis i inars esrdax melld.
I would give them to the children and they would go as well-wishers.
bavvebs gavaandi xolme da dilas midiodnen mevleebad.
ziadi olil las, bogka xda ka lzi meled i ka xgnad.
Zviad was little, he had to go over the bridge when he was going as a well-wisher and I used to see him off.
zviadi aara iqo, xidze hkonda gasavleli roca mevled midioda da gavacilebdit xolme.
eka xaqlnda, eayb adgite esrda, ere lis rda.
He was scared; he was going to such a place that he went hardly...
imaze einoda, imistana adgilas midioda, rom livs midioda xolme ("cavidoda").
eyi maqalar las i ka xagnis alyrs melld s i ean lsakare sga qednldax.
He was so much afraid! And I used to see them off all as well-wishers and then they would come back with presents.
iseti miara iqo da gavacilebdi xolme amat mevleebad qvelas da mere saukrebit brundebodnen ("emovidodnen").
eno sudenar er gaxden, pepiod eicala eno mele, sudenar er gaxden
Then, when they became students, Pepiko changed her well-wishers then...
mere sudenebi rom gaxdnen, pepiom eicvala mere mevle, sudenebi rom gaxdnen
i amenen nay guge mele geqda i gugeurad aarebdit i s xomd xasqdad
and we had our well-wisher here and made him go up and down in our own way and we did everything well.
da ak ven veni mevle gvqavda da veneburad vaarebdit da qvelapers argad vaetebdit
And I had a good family, hospitable one...
